= Volume Texture =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""Samples a volume texture baked by SideFX Labs Volume Texture Export."""

== Overview ==

Volume Texture reads back a volume texture baked with the SideFX Labs __Volume Texture Export__ tool. It reconstructs 3D color by sampling a tiled 2D texture atlas using the bounding box position and tile counts.

@parameters

Volume Texture:
    #id: volume_texture
    File path to the baked volume texture (`.rat`, `.exr`, etc.).

BB_pos:
    #id: BB
    Bounding box origin of the source volume. Connect from the original geometry's bounding box.

U_Tile:
    #id: U_Tile
    Number of horizontal tiles in the texture atlas. Must match the export setting.

V_Tile:
    #id: V_Tile
    Number of vertical tiles in the texture atlas. Must match the export setting.

@outputs

outClr:
    RGB color sampled from the volume texture at the current shading position.
